{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context / Problem\n\nThe outbound differ is the last core module that *compares* in vendor shape.\n`outbound_differ.py:39-41` imports `_diff_fields`, `_extract_jira_field`, `_assignee_matches`,\nand `_LOCAL_TO_JIRA_TYPE` from `adapters.jira.outbound_fields`; the update path\n(`_compute_outbound_update_mutation`, call at `outbound_differ.py:732`) delegates to\n`_diff_fields` (`adapters/jira/outbound_fields.py:369-618`), which maps local→Jira and then\nreads raw vendor snapshot keys (`fields.status.name`, `assignee.accountId`,\n`parent.key`, ADF `description`). These helpers have no ADR 0035 §(d)-legal home: on the\nBackend port they would force every backend to consume Jira snapshot dicts (exactly what plan\nreview blocked on the prior attempt, ticket 97f2 / Gerrit change 920); left in core they keep\nthe core vendor-shaped. Meanwhile the *inbound* differ already diffs canonically — it maps the\nvendor payload to local shape via the injected `InboundMapper` before comparing\n(`inbound_differ.py:159`). This asymmetry is the design flaw blocking epic bbf1 AC3.\n\n## Approach\n\nBring the outbound update path to parity with the inbound differ: **diff in canonical shape;\nvendor shapes cross core only as opaque payloads produced/consumed by port calls at the\nboundaries.**\n\n1. `run_differs.py` additionally passes `inbound_mapper=backend.inbound` to\n   `compute_outbound_mutations` (the backend object is already in scope there —\n   `run_differs.py:481-495` currently passes `outbound_mapper=backend.outbound`).\n2. `_compute_outbound_update_mutation` canonicalizes the snapshot entry with\n   `inbound_mapper.map_remote_to_local(jira_snapshot[jira_key])` (mirroring\n   `inbound_differ.py:159`) and compares the local ticket against the canonical remote using\n   new **neutral** field-comparison helpers in core (local vocabulary only).\n3. The changed-field set is computed in local field names; the vendor update payload is built\n   at the emission boundary by the already-injected\n   `outbound_mapper.map_local_to_remote` restricted to the changed fields — the same port\n   call the create path already uses (`outbound_differ.py:632`). `OutboundMutation.fields`\n   therefore stays vendor-shaped and the entire apply pipeline is untouched\n   (`batch_dispatch.py:107-110`, `dispatch_one.py:442-514` and the unpacked\n   `client.update_issue(issue_key, **fields)` at `dispatch_one.py:602`).\n4. Widen the Jira `InboundMapper` output (translation only, implemented in the vendor mapper\n   `inbound_fields.py:141-184` / delegate `adapters/jira/backend.py:43-47`):\n   - assignee identity aliases (displayName / emailAddress / accountId), so core replaces the\n     vendor shape-tolerant `_assignee_matches` (`adapters/jira/outbound_fields.py:237-261`)\n     with neutral membership matching, preserving the both-empty match\n     (`outbound_fields.py:251-252`);\n   - the remote parent id (from `fields.parent.key`), so core compares the\n     BindingStore-resolved expected remote key against the mapped remote key, replacing\n     `outbound_fields.py:531-558`;\n   - reporter identity aliases for the outbound one-way reporter diff\n     (`outbound_fields.py:346-366` and `:617`).\n5. Description parity: compare the port-sanitized local text\n   (`FieldSanitizer.sanitize_description`) against the mapper-decoded remote text, preserving\n   the ADF-fit + rstrip semantics of `outbound_fields.py:566-583`.\n6. Core policies stay in core, expressed on local field names: issuetype excluded on update\n   (today `outbound_fields.py:449-459`; the inbound differ already excludes `ticket_type`)\n   and inbound-directionality suppression (today `outbound_fields.py:467-470`).\n7. **The arbitration baseline is canonicalized at read time, storage unchanged.** The\n   per-binding baseline is *written* from raw remote snapshot entries and stored in vendor\n   field names/shapes (`binding_store.py:374` filters to `_BASELINE_FIELDS`,\n   `binding_store.py:71`; writers pass `prev_snapshot[jira_key]` / `curr_snapshot[jira_key]`\n   at `binding_store.py:390`, `reconcile.py:520`, `apply_inbound_records.py:212`). Per the\n   canonical-comparison principle it is a stored remote payload: it stays vendor-shaped at\n   rest (opaque; NO data migration, writers untouched), and the outbound differ's\n   suppression/conflict path applies `inbound_mapper.map_remote_to_local` to the baseline\n   entry at the same ingestion boundary as the snapshot. The vendor suppression helpers\n   (`_local_matches_prev`/`_jira_matches_prev`, which today call `_extract_jira_field` on\n   vendor-nested values) are replaced by neutral canonical-name equivalents, and the\n   outbound↔inbound field-name reconciliation (`summary` vs `title`) disappears because\n   baseline, snapshot, and local ticket all compare in local names after mapping. The Jira\n   `map_remote_to_local` must therefore tolerate a partial fields dict (the\n   `_BASELINE_FIELDS` subset) — mapping only the keys present. Other baseline consumers\n   (e.g. `binding_walk.py:192`) are out of scope and keep reading the stored vendor shape.\n8. `_diff_fields` / `_extract_jira_field` / `_assignee_matches` / `_LOCAL_TO_JIRA_TYPE` become\n   adapter-internal; the `outbound_differ.py:39-43` imports are deleted and the test-suite\n   re-exports migrate to `adapters.jira.outbound_fields`. The bound-but-absent direct-GET path\n   is unchanged: the `absent_alive_fields` return (`outbound_differ.py:432-443`, populated at\n   `:730`) remains a raw vendor dict passed through core opaquely (core never reads into it).\n9. Amend ADR 0035 §(d) (`docs/adr/0035-reconciler-vendor-adapter-seam.md`) to pin the\n   principle: *core compares only canonical shapes; the outbound differ canonicalizes the\n   snapshot via `InboundMapper` and emits vendor payloads only via `OutboundMapper`.*\n\nRejected alternatives: (a) putting the vendor-shaped comparison helpers on the port — already\nBLOCKED by plan review as an §(d) violation (port methods parameterized on `jira_fields`\ndicts); (b) re-shaping `OutboundMutation.fields` to canonical and mapping in the applier —\ntouches the whole dispatch pipeline (`batch_dispatch`/`dispatch_one`/`apply_handlers`/\n`apply_outbound`) for no additional neutrality, since emission-boundary mapping in the differ\nalready keeps vendor shape out of core logic.\n\nBehavior risk, named: the old differ compares in Jira value-space (mapped local vs raw\nremote), the new one in local value-space (local vs inbound-mapped remote). Where the\nlocal↔Jira status/priority value maps are not inverse-consistent, or the remote status does\nnot map (the inbound mapper emits `status` only when mapped, `inbound_fields.py:167-176` —\nthe neutral helper must treat canonical-status-absent + local-status-present as a diff, since\nlocal wins), decisions could drift. The characterization suite below pins decision-for-\ndecision equivalence before the old helpers are demoted.\n\n## Scope\n\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_differ.py (canonical comparison; neutral helpers; emission-boundary mapping)\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/run_differs.py (pass inbound_mapper=backend.inbound)\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_backend.py (InboundMapper contract note: canonical output incl. identity aliases + parent remote id)\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_fields.py (Jira mapper: aliases, parent remote id, reporter aliases)\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/backend.py (delegate surface)\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/outbound_fields.py (helpers become adapter-internal)\n- docs/adr/0035-reconciler-vendor-adapter-seam.md (§(d) canonical-comparison amendment)\n- tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_neutrality.py (AST gate extended to outbound_differ.py)\n- tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/ (new characterization suite; migrated re-export tests)\n\n## Testing\n\n- Happy path: a bound ticket with one changed field emits an update whose vendor payload\n  equals today's (port-mapped); an unchanged ticket emits nothing.\n- Characterization (old-vs-new decision equivalence): identical emit/no-emit decisions and\n  payloads across the full local↔Jira status and priority value maps; assignee shapes\n  (accountId / emailAddress / displayName / both-empty); absent parent and parent change;\n  ADF description fit+rstrip; inbound-directionality suppression driven by a vendor-shaped\n  stored baseline (suppression still fires after canonicalization — the regression the old\n  shape mismatch would silently cause is unconditional local-wins); conflict detection via\n  the canonicalized baseline; a partial `_BASELINE_FIELDS` subset dict through\n  `map_remote_to_local`; unmapped remote status.\n- Runtime proof: the update path builds its payload exclusively via the injected\n  `OutboundMapper` (mirroring `test_outbound_differ_uses_injected_mapper`,\n  `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_neutrality.py:189-213`).\n- Edge: snapshot entry missing/deleted sentinels (`_DELETED`/`_TRANSPORT_ERROR`) behave as\n  today; `absent_alive_fields` passthrough unchanged.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `outbound_differ.py` contains NO `adapters.jira` import (module-level or\n      function-nested) — verified by the extended AST case in\n      `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_neutrality.py`.\n- [ ] The update path canonicalizes the snapshot via the injected `InboundMapper` before any\n      comparison, and no core code reads vendor snapshot keys (`status.name`, `accountId`,\n      `parent.key`, ADF) — those reads exist only under `adapters/jira/` — verified by the\n      neutrality gate + code review.\n- [ ] The characterization suite proving old-vs-new decision equivalence (cases enumerated in\n      Testing) is green — verified by `pytest` on the new test file.\n- [ ] ADR 0035 §(d) records the canonical-comparison principle — verified by the amended ADR\n      text in the change.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` green; whole test tree collects with 0 errors."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784821984562762001,"uuid":"2b9ce027-9c8e-49b2-bfa4-29c775e0a552"}